{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775877787295,"sessionID":"ses_285703b89ffecpRDQILMzEYYNL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a908e9d001wY7Y2beg8dyYa1","messageID":"msg_d7a908965001PoXgyiAgXiNXfS","sessionID":"ses_285703b89ffecpRDQILMzEYYNL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877801512,"sessionID":"ses_285703b89ffecpRDQILMzEYYNL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a90c6100010cB2WZRqB8tc3L","messageID":"msg_d7a908965001PoXgyiAgXiNXfS","sessionID":"ses_285703b89ffecpRDQILMzEYYNL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-1b197e8b6ad0468a9603091a5ed06e1a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document outlines the architecture and implementation approach for the AgentRuntimeClient, a Python SDK client that provides a high-level interface for managing agents and their runtime sessions.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n1. **AgentRuntimeClient** - Main client class for API interactions\n2. **Agent Management Layer** - Handles CRUD operations for agents\n3. **Runtime Operations Layer** - Manages agent lifecycle and sessions\n4. **Error Handling Layer** - Centralized exception handling\n5. **HTTP Client** - Underlying HTTP communication (using httpx)\n6. **Data Models** - Pydantic models for type-safe data handling\n\n### Design Patterns\n\n- **Builder Pattern** - For agent configuration\n- **Repository Pattern** - For agent and session management\n- **Strategy Pattern** - For different runtime types\n- **Factory Pattern** - For creating agents and sessions\n\n## Class Structure\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(self, base_url: str, api_key: Optional[str] = None, ...)\n    \n    # Agent Management\n    async def create_agent(self, config: AgentConfig, ...) -> Agent\n    async def get_agent(self, agent_id: str) -> Agent\n    async def list_agents(self, ...) -> List[Agent]\n    async def update_agent(self, agent_id: str, config: AgentConfig) -> Agent\n    async def delete_agent(self, agent_id: str) -> None\n    \n    # Runtime Operations\n    async def start_agent(self, agent_id: str, ...) -> RuntimeSession\n    async def stop_agent(self, session_id: str, ...) -> None\n    async def get_session_status(self, session_id: str) -> RuntimeSession\n    async def list_sessions(self, ...) -> List[RuntimeSession]\n    \n    # Private methods\n    async def _make_request(self, method: str, path: str, ...) -> Response\n    def _handle_error(self, response: Response) -> None\n```\n\n### Data Models\n\nAll data models inherit from Pydantic's `BaseModel` for automatic validation and serialization.\n\n## Error Handling Strategy\n\n1. **HTTP Errors** - Map HTTP status codes to appropriate exceptions\n2. **Validation Errors** - Use Pydantic's validation for input data\n3. **Network Errors** - Implement retry logic with exponential backoff\n4. **Custom Exceptions** - Create specific exception types for better error handling\n\n## Async/Await Design\n\n- All public methods are async to avoid blocking\n- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` for non-blocking HTTP requests\n- Provide methods for both sync and async operations (future enhancement)\n\n## Configuration Management\n\n### Client Configuration\n\n```python\n- base_url: str (required)\n- api_key: Optional[str]\n- timeout: int = 30\n- max_retries: int = 3\n- retry_delay: float = 1.0\n```\n\n### Agent Configuration\n\n```python\n- runtime_config: RuntimeConfig\n- capabilities: List[str]\n- constraints: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]\n- resources: Optional[ResourceConfig]\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n- Test each method in isolation\n- Mock HTTP responses\n- Test error handling\n- Test data model validation\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n- Test against real AgentRuntime service\n- Test end-to-end workflows\n- Test error scenarios\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **API Key Management** - Secure storage of API keys\n2. **TLS/SSL** - Enforce HTTPS for all communications\n3. **Input Validation** - Strict validation of all inputs\n4. **Rate Limiting** - Respect service rate limits\n5. **Error Messages** - Avoid exposing sensitive information\n\n## Performance Optimization\n\n1. **Connection Pooling** - Reuse HTTP connections\n2. **Caching** - Cache frequently accessed data (optional)\n3. **Batch Operations** - Support batch operations where possible\n4. **Timeouts** - Implement appropriate timeouts to prevent hanging\n\n## Logging and Monitoring\n\n1. **Structured Logging** - Use structured logging format\n2. **Request/Response Logging** - Log API calls (with sensitive data redacted)\n3. **Performance Metrics** - Track request latency and success rates\n4. **Error Tracking** - Track and alert on errors\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Sync API** - Provide synchronous versions of methods\n2. **Streaming** - Support streaming responses for long-running operations\n3. **Webhooks** - Support webhook notifications\n4. **Event System** - Provide event-based API for agent lifecycle events\n5. **Retry Strategies** - Configurable retry strategies\n6. **Request Signing** - Support for request signing for enhanced security","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","time":{"start":1775877801507,"end":1775877801511}}}}
