{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877860862,"sessionID":"ses_285703b89ffecpRDQILMzEYYNL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a91ade3001ovFjwsAEn0ZECs","messageID":"msg_d7a915b9a001CDEeLoHz6HAYfV","sessionID":"ses_285703b89ffecpRDQILMzEYYNL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-60dca6fceb2f4c60b426e1935e0cc28f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Implementation Tasks\n\n## Phase 1: Core Infrastructure (Week 1-2)\n\n### 1.1 Project Setup\n- [ ] Create package directory structure\n- [ ] Set up pyproject.toml with dependencies\n- [ ] Configure development dependencies (pytest, mypy, black, etc.)\n- [ ] Create __init__.py files\n- [ ] Set up test directory structure\n\n### 1.2 Base HTTP Client\n- [ ] Implement base HTTP client class\n- [ ] Add authentication handling (API key in headers)\n- [ ] Implement retry logic with exponential backoff\n- [ ] Add timeout configuration\n- [ ] Implement error handling and response parsing\n- [ ] Add logging setup\n\n### 1.3 Data Models\n- [ ] Create Agent model\n- [ ] Create AgentConfig model\n- [ ] Create RuntimeConfig model\n- [ ] Create ResourceConfig model\n- [ ] Create RuntimeSession model\n- [ ] Create AgentStatus enum\n- [ ] Create SessionStatus enum\n- [ ] Add Pydantic validators\n- [ ] Write unit tests for all models\n\n### 1.4 Exception Hierarchy\n- [ ] Create AgentRuntimeException base class\n- [ ] Create AuthenticationError exception\n- [ ] Create ConnectionError exception\n- [ ] Create AgentError base class and subclasses\n- [ ] Create RuntimeError base class and subclasses\n- [ ] Create ValidationError exception\n- [ ] Implement error mapping from HTTP status codes\n- [ ] Write unit tests for exceptions\n\n## Phase 2: Agent Management (Week 3-4)\n\n### 2.1 Create Agent\n- [ ] Implement create_agent method\n- [ ] Add request validation\n- [ ] Handle response parsing\n- [ ] Add error handling\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n- [ ] Write integration tests\n\n### 2.2 Get Agent\n- [ ] Implement get_agent method\n- [ ] Add not found handling\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n- [ ] Write integration tests\n\n### 2.3 List Agents\n- [ ] Implement list_agents method\n- [ ] Add filtering by workspace_id\n- [ ] Add filtering by status\n- [ ] Implement pagination (limit, offset)\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n- [ ] Write integration tests\n\n### 2.4 Update Agent\n- [ ] Implement update_agent method\n- [ ] Add request validation\n- [ ] Handle partial updates\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n- [ ] Write integration tests\n\n### 2.5 Delete Agent\n- [ ] Implement delete_agent method\n- [ ] Add not found handling\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n- [ ] Write integration tests\n\n## Phase 3: Runtime Operations (Week 5-6)\n\n### 3.1 Start Agent\n- [ ] Implement start_agent method\n- [ ] Add input data handling\n- [ ] Handle session creation\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n- [ ] Write integration tests\n\n### 3.2 Stop Agent\n- [ ] Implement stop_agent method\n- [ ] Add graceful shutdown support\n- [ ] Handle not found scenarios\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n- [ ] Write integration tests\n\n### 3.3 Get Session Status\n- [ ] Implement get_session_status method\n- [ ] Add not found handling\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n- [ ] Write integration tests\n\n### 3.4 List Sessions\n- [ ] Implement list_sessions method\n- [ ] Add filtering by agent_id\n- [ ] Add filtering by status\n- [ ] Implement pagination\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n- [ ] Write integration tests\n\n## Phase 4: Testing and Documentation (Week 7-8)\n\n### 4.1 Unit Tests\n- [ ] Achieve >90% code coverage\n- [ ] Test all public methods\n- [ ] Test error handling paths\n- [ ] Test data model validation\n- [ ] Add edge case tests\n\n### 4.2 Integration Tests\n- [ ] Set up test environment\n- [ ] Mock AgentRuntime service responses\n- [ ] Test end-to-end workflows\n- [ ] Test authentication scenarios\n- [ ] Test error scenarios\n\n### 4.3 Documentation\n- [ ] Write module docstrings\n- [ ] Write class docstrings\n- [ ] Write method docstrings\n- [ ] Add parameter descriptions\n- [ ] Add return type descriptions\n- [ ] Add exception documentation\n- [ ] Add usage examples\n\n### 4.4 Usage Examples\n- [ ] Create basic usage example\n- [ ] Create agent lifecycle example\n- [ ] Create session management example\n- [ ] Create error handling example\n- [ ] Add examples to documentation\n\n### 4.5 Performance Testing\n- [ ] Benchmark common operations\n- [ ] Test with high concurrency\n- [ ] Identify bottlenecks\n- [ ] Optimize hot paths\n- [ ] Document performance characteristics\n\n## Phase 5: Review and Release (Week 9-10)\n\n### 5.1 Code Review\n- [ ] Self-review all code\n- [ ] Check for consistency\n- [ ] Verify error handling\n- [ ] Check type annotations\n- [ ] Review test coverage\n\n### 5.2 Bug Fixes\n- [ ] Fix any bugs found during review\n- [ ] Add tests for bug fixes\n- [ ] Update documentation as needed\n\n### 5.3 Release Preparation\n- [ ] Update CHANGE.md\n- [ ] Update README.md with implementation details\n- [ ] Verify all dependencies are correct\n- [ ] Check version number\n- [ ] Prepare release notes\n\n### 5.4 Documentation Review\n- [ ] Review all documentation\n- [ ] Check for clarity\n- [ ] Verify examples work\n- [ ] Check for completeness\n- [ ] Get feedback from peers\n\n## Additional Tasks\n\n### Configuration\n- [ ] Add configuration file support\n- [ ] Add environment variable support\n- [ ] Document configuration options\n\n### Logging\n- [ ] Implement structured logging\n- [ ] Add request/response logging\n- [ ] Add performance logging\n- [ ] Document log levels\n\n### Type Checking\n- [ ] Run mypy on entire codebase\n- [ ] Fix any type errors\n- [ ] Add type stubs if needed\n- [ ] Configure mypy for strict mode\n\n### Code Quality\n- [ ] Run black formatter\n- [ ] Run flake8 linter\n- [ ] Fix any linting issues\n- [ ] Add pre-commit hooks\n\n### CI/CD\n- [ ] Set up GitHub Actions\n- [ ] Add linting step\n- [ ] Add type checking step\n- [ ] Add unit test step\n- [ ] Add integration test step\n- [ ] 